# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Eric YT Channel AI — environment variables
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# For local use you can ignore this file entirely. The defaults already work:
# the app starts on http://localhost:3000, the database lives in ./data, and
# no auth is required.
#
# All integration API keys (Claude, Deepgram, YouTube, Apify, Exa, Gemini)
# are entered INSIDE the running app at /integrations — NOT here. They get
# stored in the local SQLite database, which means they survive restarts and
# are never committed to git.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` only if you want to override one of the settings
# below. `.env` is gitignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Override the data folder location. By default the app uses `./data` next
# to package.json — solid default, do not change unless you have a specific
# reason (e.g. you want the DB on an external drive).
# DATA_DIR=/absolute/path/to/data

# Basic Auth gate. Leave blank locally. Only set both if you ever expose the
# app to the internet (e.g. via ngrok / Tailscale Funnel) and want a login
# prompt in front of it.
# APP_USERNAME=
# APP_PASSWORD=
